ceptable; without it, the policy reduces the chance of pulling a tampered image but is not a\n           substitue for digest pinning.\n\n    --- SECTION 4: JOB / POD SECURITY CONTEXT ---\n\n    [GAP]  spark-master deployment: pod-level securityContext is empty ({}). No runAsNonRoot, runAsUser,\n           fsGroup, or seccompProfile configured. Container may run as root (UID 0).\n\n    [GAP]  spark-worker deployment: pod-level securityContext is empty ({}). Same issues as spark-master.\n\n    [GAP]  spark-pi job: pod-level securityContext is empty ({}). The spark-submit container runs with no\n           security restrictions.\n\n    [GAP]  No container-level securityContext is set on any container. Specifically missing:\n             - allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n             - readOnlyRootFilesystem: true (or explicit false with justification)\n             - capabilities.drop: [\"ALL\"]\n             - runAsNonRoot: true\n           These omissions mean containers have the default (permissive) Linux capability set and may\n           run as root, violating least-privilege and CIS Kubernetes Benchmark controls 5.2.x.\n\n    --- SECTION 5: NETWORK POLICIES ---\n\n    [GAP]  No NetworkPolicy resources exist in the spark-pi namespace. All pods can freely communicate\n           with any other pod in any namespace and can initiate outbound connections without restriction.\n           Recommend adding a default-deny ingress/egress policy and explicit allow rules for only the\n           required Spark traffic (driver ↔ master port 7077, master ↔ worker port 8081, web UI port 8080).\n\n    --- SUMMARY ---\n\n    Correctly configured (PASS): 7 controls\n      - Dedicated service account (not default)\n      - Namespace-scoped Role only (no ClusterRole)\n      - RoleBinding correctly wired\n      - No cluster-wide RBAC grants\n      - Resource requests and limits set on all three workloads\n      - Specific image version tag used (not 'latest')\n\n    Gaps requiring remediation: 6 controls\n      1. [RBAC]     Role grants overly broad verbs (delete/update/patch on pods/configmaps/pvcs).\n      2. [IMAGE]    No image digest (sha256) pinning — mutable tags in use.\n      3. [SECCTX]   spark-master pod security context absent — potential root execution.\n      4. [SECCTX]   spark-worker pod security context absent — potential root execution.\n      5. [SECCTX]   spark-pi job pod security context absent — potential root execution; no privilege\n                    drop, no allowPrivilegeEscalation:false, no capability restrictions on any container.\n      6. [NETPOL]   No NetworkPolicy — unrestricted inter-namespace and egress traffic.\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  creationTimestamp: \"2026-06-16T10:05:38Z\"\n  name: config-audit\n  namespace: spark-pi\n  resourceVersion: \"62742\"\n  uid: a60bb9c6-b1c7-4fff-9537-cb921f8144b9","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
