{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CSbR19obeXz9p5Usy8WHG4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the configmap doesn't exist yet. Now let me write the plan. I need to be careful about escaping in bash. I'll write it to a temp file first, then create the ConfigMap from file.\n\nLet me organize my findings:\n\n**Current State Summary:**\n- spark-master: apache/spark:3.5.3, cpu req=200m lim=500m, mem req=512Mi lim=1Gi, 1 replica, no securityContext\n- spark-worker: apache/spark:3.5.3, same resources, 1 replica, SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G, SPARK_WORKER_CORES=1, no securityContext\n- spark-pi Job: apache/spark:3.5.3, same resources, running locally with --master local[2] instead of using the cluster, --driver-memory 512m, 1000 iterations, backoffLimit=0, already completed\n- Service: spark-master ClusterIP on 7077 and 8080\n- RBAC: Role with overly broad verbs including delete on pods, proper RoleBinding, dedicated SA\n- No NetworkPolicies, no security contexts on any workload, no image digest pinning\n\n**Changes to plan:**\n1. RBAC tightening (lowest risk)\n2. Image digest pinning (requires rolling restarts)\n3. Security context hardening (requires restarts)\n4. Network policy enforcement (traffic-affecting)\n5. Fix job's --master to use the cluster instead of local[2]\n6. Consider worker scaling for production HA\n\nNow I'm writing out the plan to a temp file to avoid shell escaping complications.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1805,"cache_read_input_tokens":35383,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1805},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7ed9bf79-e2dd-4c8c-a459-ba0f89715c35","uuid":"e0e27b33-86f8-4825-a752-34ed7b817332","re