{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CSbR19obeXz9p5Usy8WHG4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Bd2GXGrxAf6Pvg8AGJHhHA","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/spark-pi-change-plan.md","content":"# Spark-Pi Namespace — Maintenance Upgrade Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-16  \n**Scope:** spark-pi namespace  \n**Status:** DRAFT — awaiting team review before execution  \n**Basis:** Live inspection of cluster state + config-audit ConfigMap findings\n\n---\n\n## Current State (as-found)\n\n| Resource | Key Settings |\n|---|---|\n| spark-master Deployment | image: apache/spark:3.5.3, replicas: 1, cpu req/lim: 200m/500m, mem req/lim: 512Mi/1Gi, no securityContext |\n| spark-worker Deployment | image: apache/spark:3.5.3, replicas: 1, same resource limits, SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=1G, SPARK_WORKER_CORES=1, no securityContext |\n| spark-pi Job | image: apache/spark:3.5.3, --master local[2] (bypasses cluster), --driver-memory 512m, 1000 iterations, backoffLimit: 0, Completed |\n| Service spark-master | ClusterIP, ports 7077 (spark) and 8080 (webui) |\n| RBAC | Role spark-pi-role: full CRUD + delete on pods/configmaps/pvcs/services; SA spark-pi; no ClusterRole |\n| Network Policies | None — unrestricted inter-namespace and egress |\n| Security Contexts | None on any workload (all pods may run as root) |\n| Image Pinning | Tag-only (apache/spark:3.5.3) — no sha256 digest |\n\n---\n\n## Identified Gaps (from config-audit + inspection)\n\n1. **[RBAC]** Role grants `delete`, `update`, `patch` on `pods` — overly broad; a compromised driver could terminate arbitrary pods.\n2. **[IMAGE]** Mutable image tags in use; no sha256 digest pinning across all three workloads.\n3. **[SECCTX]** All three workloads (spark-master, spark-worker, spark-pi job) lack pod- and container-level security contexts: no `runAsNonRoot`, no `allowPrivilegeEscalation: false`, no capability dropping.\n4. **[NETPOL]** No NetworkPolicy — all pods freely communicate with any namespace and initiate unrestricted egress.\n5. **[JOB-CONFIG]** The spark-pi Job uses `--master local[2]`, running entirely inside the driver pod. The deployed spark-master and spark-worker cluster is not used. Future job runs should submit to `spark://spark-master:7077`.\n6. **[CAPACITY]** Single spark-worker replica with 1 core and 1G memory provides no fault tolerance. Production workloads warrant at least 2 replicas.\n\n---\n\n## Upgrade Steps\n\nExecute in the order below. Each step is self-contained and must be verified before proceeding to the next. Do NOT apply changes during active job runs; wait for the spark-pi job to complete (currently Completed — safe to proceed).\n\n---\n\n### Step 1 — RBAC: Tighten Role Verbs\n\n**Risk:** Low (no pod restarts required)  \n**Change:** Remove the `delete` verb from `pods` in `spark-pi-role`. Restrict `update` and `patch` to `configmaps` only (needed for Spark configuration), remove them from `pods`, `services`, and `persistentvolumeclaims` unless a specific use case is identified.\n\n**Target role rules (apply with `kubectl apply`):**\n```yaml\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"pods\"]\n  verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"services\"]\n  verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"configmaps\"]\n  verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"persistentvolumeclaims\"]\n  verbs: [\"create\", \"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n```\n\n**Verification:**\n```bash\nkubectl auth can-i delete pods --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi\n# Expected: no\nkubectl auth can-i get pods --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi\n# Expected: yes\nkubectl get role spark-pi-role -n spark-pi -o yaml | grep -A20 rules\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 2 — Image: Pin to sha256 Digest\n\n**Risk:** Low-Medium (triggers rolling restart of both deployments and requires re-creating the Job template)  \n**Change:** Replace the mutable tag `apache/spark:3.5.3` with a sha256-pinned reference on all three workloads. Before applying, pull the image and record the digest:\n\n```bash\ndocker pull apache/spark:3.5.3\ndocker inspect apache/spark:3.5.3 --format='{{index .RepoDigests 0}}'\n# Record the output, e.g.: apache/spark@sha256:<64-char-hex>\n```\n\nUpdate all three image fields to: `apache/spark@sha256:<digest>`  \nKeep `imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent` (acceptable with digest pinning; the digest guarantees identity).\n\n**Verification:**\n```bash\nkubectl get deploy spark-master spark-worker -n spark-pi \\\n  -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}: {.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}{\"\\n\"}{end}'\n# Both lines must contain \"sha256:\" not just \"3.5.3\"\nkubectl rollout status deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi\n# Both must show \"successfully rolled out\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 3 — Security Contexts: Enforce Non-Root and Drop Capabilities\n\n**Risk:** Medium (rolling restarts; Spark may write logs/tmp to the container filesystem — test in staging first)  \n**Change:** Add pod- and container-level security contexts to spark-master and spark-worker deployments. Apache Spark's official image creates a `spark` user at UID 185; use that UID.\n\n**Pod-level securityContext (both deployments):**\n```yaml\nsecurityContext:\n  runAsNonRoot: true\n  runAsUser: 185\n  runAsGroup: 185\n  fsGroup: 185\n```\n\n**Container-level securityContext (each container):**\n```yaml\nsecurityContext:\n  allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n  capabilities:\n    drop: [\"ALL\"]\n```\n\nNote: Do NOT set `readOnlyRootFilesystem: true` without first mounting writable emptyDir volumes at `/opt/spark/logs` and `/opt/spark/work`. Spark writes logs and temp files at runtime. The safer upgrade path is to add `readOnlyRootFilesystem: true` as a follow-on change after confirming volume mounts work.\n\nApply the same pod-level and container-level securityContext to the spark-pi Job template. Since the Job has already completed, update its stored spec so the next invocation inherits the settings (delete and recreate the Job or update a CronJob/Helm chart that manages it).\n\n**Verification:**\n```bash\nkubectl rollout status deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi\n# Both must show \"successfully rolled out\"\nkubectl exec -n spark-pi deploy/spark-master -- id\n# Must show: uid=185(spark) gid=185(spark)\nkubectl exec -n spark-pi deploy/spark-worker -- id\n# Must show: uid=185(spark) gid=185(spark)\nkubectl get deploy spark-master -n spark-pi \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.securityContext}'\n# Must contain runAsNonRoot:true, runAsUser:185\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 4 — Network Policies: Default-Deny + Explicit Allow\n\n**Risk:** Medium-High (takes effect immediately; misconfiguration silently drops traffic)  \n**Change:** Apply a default-deny policy first, then add explicit allow rules. Test connectivity between master and worker after each apply.\n\n**4a. Default-deny ingress (apply first in a staging environment):**\n```yaml\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: NetworkPolicy\nmetadata:\n  name: default-deny-ingress\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  podSelector: {}\n  policyTypes: [Ingress]\n```\n\n**4b. Allow Spark internal traffic:**\n```yaml\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: NetworkPolicy\nmetadata:\n  name: allow-spark-internal\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  podSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: spark-master\n  policyTypes: [Ingress]\n  ingress:\n  - from:\n    - namespaceSelector:\n        matchLabels:\n          kubernetes.io/metadata.name: spark-pi\n    ports:\n    - port: 7077  # Spark RPC\n    - port: 8080  # Web UI\n```\n\n**4c. Allow worker ingress from master:**\n```yaml\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: NetworkPolicy\nmetadata:\n  name: allow-worker-ingress\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  podSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: spark-worker\n  policyTypes: [Ingress]\n  ingress:\n  - from:\n    - namespaceSelector:\n        matchLabels:\n          kubernetes.io/metadata.name: spark-pi\n    ports:\n    - port: 8081  # Worker web UI / executor port\n```\n\n**Verification:**\n```bash\nkubectl get networkpolicies -n spark-pi\n# Must list: default-deny-ingress, allow-spark-internal, allow-worker-ingress\n# Confirm master-worker connectivity:\nWORKER_IP=$(kubectl get pod -n spark-pi -l app=spark-worker -o jsonpath='{.items[0].status.podIP}')\nkubectl exec -n spark-pi deploy/spark-master -- nc -zv \"$WORKER_IP\" 8081\n# Expected: Connection succeeded\n# Confirm master web UI reachable from within namespace:\nkubectl exec -n spark-pi deploy/spark-worker -- nc -zv spark-master 8080\n# Expected: Connection succeeded\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 5 — Job Configuration: Point to Cluster Master\n\n**Risk:** Low (affects only future Job runs; existing completed Job is unchanged)  \n**Change:** Update the spark-pi Job's `--master` flag from `local[2]` to `spark://spark-master:7077`. This makes the job actually utilize the deployed spark-master and spark-worker, rather than running a local mini-cluster inside the driver pod. Also consider increasing `backoffLimit` from 0 to 2 so transient failures (e.g., master not yet Ready) can self-heal.\n\n**Updated spark-submit command:**\n```bash\n/opt/spark/bin/spark-submit \\\n  --master spark://spark-master:7077 \\\n  --driver-memory 512m \\\n  --executor-memory 768m \\\n  --class org.apache.spark.examples.SparkPi \\\n  /opt/spark/examples/jars/spark-examples_2.12-3.5.3.jar \\\n  1000\n```\n\nNote: If digest pinning (Step 2) has been applied, update the jar path if needed to match the new image reference.\n\n**Verification:**\n```bash\n# Delete the completed Job and recreate with the updated spec:\nkubectl delete job spark-pi -n spark-pi\nkubectl apply -f spark-pi-job-updated.yaml\n# Watch the job:\nkubectl get job spark-pi -n spark-pi -w\n# Expected: COMPLETIONS transitions to 1/1\n# Verify the driver connected to the master (not local mode):\nkubectl logs -n spark-pi -l job-name=spark-pi | grep \"Master URL\"\n# Must show: spark://spark-master:7077\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 6 — Capacity: Scale spark-worker to 2 Replicas\n\n**Risk:** Low (adds capacity, no disruption to existing replica)  \n**Change:** Scale `spark-worker` Deployment to `replicas: 2` to provide fault tolerance and allow the pi job to distribute executors across two nodes.\n\n```bash\nkubectl scale deploy spark-worker -n spark-pi --replicas=2\n```\n\n**Verification:**\n```bash\nkubectl get deploy spark-worker -n spark-pi\n# READY must show 2/2\nkubectl get pods -n spark-pi -l app=spark-worker\n# Must list 2 Running pods\n# After a job run, confirm both workers appear in the Spark master UI:\nkubectl port-forward svc/spark-master 8080:8080 -n spark-pi\n# Browse to http://localhost:8080 — Workers section must list 2 alive workers\n```\n\n---\n\n## Rollback Procedures\n\n| Step | Rollback Command |\n|---|---|\n| Step 1 (RBAC) | `kubectl apply -f spark-pi-role-original.yaml` (restore original verbs) |\n| Step 2 (Image) | Edit deployments to revert image to `apache/spark:3.5.3`; `kubectl rollout undo deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi` |\n| Step 3 (SecCtx) | `kubectl rollout undo deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi` |\n| Step 4 (NetPol) | `kubectl delete networkpolicy default-deny-ingress allow-spark-internal allow-worker-ingress -n spark-pi` |\n| Step 5 (Job) | Delete updated Job, recreate with original `--master local[2]` spec |\n| Step 6 (Scale) | `kubectl scale deploy spark-worker -n spark-pi --replicas=1` |\n\n**Before any step:** Save original manifests:\n```bash\nkubectl get deploy spark-master spark-worker -n spark-pi -o yaml > spark-deployments-backup.yaml\nkubectl get role spark-pi-role -n spark-pi -o yaml > spark-rbac-backup.yaml\nkubectl get job spark-pi -n spark-pi -o yaml > spark-job-backup.yaml\n```\n\n---\n\n## Post-Upgrade Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Both deployments (spark-master, spark-worker) are `Available` and `Progressing` conditions True\n- [ ] Both worker pods show `uid=185` when `id` is run inside the container\n- [ ] `kubectl auth can-i delete pods --as=system:serviceaccount:spark-pi:spark-pi -n spark-pi` returns `no`\n- [ ] All images use sha256 digest in `kubectl get deploy -o yaml`\n- [ ] `kubectl get networkpolicies -n spark-pi` lists all 3 policies\n- [ ] Re-run the spark-pi Job; it completes successfully and logs show `spark://spark-master:7077` as the master\n- [ ] 2 worker replicas visible in Spark master web UI\n- [ ] No increase in pod restart count: `kubectl get pods -n spark-pi`\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1805,"cache_read_input_tokens":35383,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1805},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7ed9bf79-e2dd-4c8c-a459-ba0f89715c35","uuid":"5c00c9a3-212c-4cef-ad17-dab5b179a249","request_id":"req_011Cc6kdWfCB3Mgf6gvRTob8"}
