rk@sha256:<digest>\nKeep imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent (acceptable with digest pinning).\n\nVerification:\n```bash\nkubectl get deploy spark-master spark-worker -n spark-pi \\\n  -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}: {.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}{\"\\n\"}{end}'\n# Both lines must contain \"sha256:\" not just \"3.5.3\"\n\nkubectl rollout status deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi\n# Both must show \"successfully rolled out\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 3 — Security Contexts: Enforce Non-Root and Drop Capabilities\n\nRisk: Medium (rolling restarts; test in staging — Spark writes logs/tmp to container filesystem)\n\nChange: Add pod- and container-level security contexts to spark-master and spark-worker. Apache Spark's official image creates a spark user at UID 185.\n\nPod-level securityContext (both deployments):\n```yaml\nsecurityContext:\n  runAsNonRoot: true\n  runAsUser: 185\n  runAsGroup: 185\n  fsGroup: 185\n```\n\nContainer-level securityContext (each container):\n```yaml\nsecurityContext:\n  allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n  capabilities:\n    drop: [\"ALL\"]\n```\n\nNote: Do NOT set readOnlyRootFilesystem: true without first mounting writable emptyDir volumes at /opt/spark/logs and /opt/spark/work. Add that as a follow-on change after confirming volume mounts work.\n\nApply the same contexts to the spark-pi Job template for future runs.\n\nVerification:\n```bash\nkubectl rollout status deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi\n# Both must show \"successfully rolled out\"\n\nkubectl exec -n spark-pi deploy/spark-master -- id\n# Must show: uid=185(spark) gid=185(spark)\n\nkubectl exec -n spark-pi deploy/spark-worker -- id\n# Must show: uid=185(spark) gid=185(spark)\n\nkubectl get deploy spark-master -n spark-pi \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.securityContext}'\n# Must contain runAsNonRoot:true, runAsUser:185\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 4 — Network Policies: Default-Deny + Explicit Allow\n\nRisk: Medium-High (takes effect immediately; misconfiguration silently drops traffic — validate in staging)\n\nChange: Apply default-deny first, then explicit allow rules.\n\n4a. Default-deny ingress:\n```yaml\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: NetworkPolicy\nmetadata:\n  name: default-deny-ingress\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  podSelector: {}\n  policyTypes: [Ingress]\n```\n\n4b. Allow Spark master ingress (from within namespace):\n```yaml\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: NetworkPolicy\nmetadata:\n  name: allow-spark-master-ingress\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  podSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: spark-master\n  policyTypes: [Ingress]\n  ingress:\n  - from:\n    - namespaceSelector:\n        matchLabels:\n          kubernetes.io/metadata.name: spark-pi\n    ports:\n    - port: 7077\n    - port: 8080\n```\n\n4c. Allow Spark worker ingress (from within namespace):\n```yaml\napiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\nkind: NetworkPolicy\nmetadata:\n  name: allow-spark-worker-ingress\n  namespace: spark-pi\nspec:\n  podSelector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: spark-worker\n  policyTypes: [Ingress]\n  ingress:\n  - from:\n    - namespaceSelector:\n        matchLabels:\n          kubernetes.io/metadata.name: spark-pi\n    ports:\n    - port: 8081\n```\n\nVerification:\n```bash\nkubectl get networkpolicies -n spark-pi\n# Must list: default-deny-ingress, allow-spark-master-ingress, allow-spark-worker-ingress\n\nWORKER_IP=$(kubectl get pod -n spark-pi -l app=spark-worker \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.items[0].status.podIP}')\nkubectl exec -n spark-pi deploy/spark-master -- nc -zv \"$WORKER_IP\" 8081\n# Expected: Connection succeeded\n\nkubectl exec -n spark-pi deploy/spark-worker -- nc -zv spark-master 8080\n# Expected: Connection succeeded\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 5 — Job Configuration: Use Cluster Master\n\nRisk: Low (affects only future Job runs; completed Job is unchanged)\n\nChange: Update the spark-pi Job spec to submit to spark://spark-master:7077 instead of local[2]. Also raise backoffLimit from 0 to 2 so transient failures (e.g., master not yet Ready) can self-heal.\n\nUpdated spark-submit invocation:\n```bash\n/opt/spark/bin/spark-submit \\\n  --master spark://spark-master:7077 \\\n  --driver-memory 512m \\\n  --executor-memory 768m \\\n  --class org.apache.spark.examples.SparkPi \\\n  /opt/spark/examples/jars/spark-examples_2.12-3.5.3.jar \\\n  1000\n```\n\nVerification:\n```bash\nkubectl delete job spark-pi -n spark-pi\nkubectl apply -f spark-pi-job-updated.yaml\n\nkubectl get job spark-pi -n spark-pi -w\n# COMPLETIONS must transition to 1/1\n\nkubectl logs -n spark-pi -l job-name=spark-pi | grep \"Master URL\"\n# Must show: spark://spark-master:7077\n```\n\n---\n\n### Step 6 — Capacity: Scale spark-worker to 2 Replicas\n\nRisk: Low (adds capacity, no disruption to existing replica)\n\nChange: Scale spark-worker Deployment to replicas: 2.\n\n```bash\nkubectl scale deploy spark-worker -n spark-pi --replicas=2\n```\n\nVerification:\n```bash\nkubectl get deploy spark-worker -n spark-pi\n# READY must show 2/2\n\nkubectl get pods -n spark-pi -l app=spark-worker\n# Must list 2 Running pods\n\n# After a job run, confirm both workers appear in the Spark master web UI:\nkubectl port-forward svc/spark-master 8080:8080 -n spark-pi\n# Browse to http://localhost:8080 — Workers section must list 2 alive workers\n```\n\n---\n\n## Rollback Procedures\n\nBefore any step, save original manifests:\n```bash\nkubectl get deploy spark-master spark-worker -n spark-pi -o yaml > spark-deployments-backup.yaml\nkubectl get role spark-pi-role -n spark-pi -o yaml > spark-rbac-backup.yaml\nkubectl get job spark-pi -n spark-pi -o yaml > spark-job-backup.yaml\n```\n\n| Step | Rollback Command |\n|---|---|\n| Step 1 (RBAC) | kubectl apply -f spark-rbac-backup.yaml |\n| Step 2 (Image) | kubectl rollout undo deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi |\n| Step 3 (SecCtx) | kubectl rollout undo deploy/spark-master deploy/spark-worker -n spark-pi |\n| Step 4 (NetPol